--- !u!114 &272702912
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 272702908}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ea1c59ace054e0f4cb9e17e1e77a9b89, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueTrigger
  dialogueBox: {fileID: 675544830}
  textComponent: {fileID: 1830359573}
  lines:
  - He showed her how to create a spell charm.
  - "He taught her two spells before the lesson was complete. She practised each
    until the pen responded without hesitation \u2014 not because she had memorised
    the strokes, but because she had understood what each one was for."
  - "The sun moved on. She watched it happen in real time \u2014 the beam of light
    that had given the Warrior his life slowly tracking across the arena floor. "
  - 'The Warrior felt it too. She could see it: the way his movements grew slightly
    slower, the way his voice, when he spoke the last instruction, carried a note
    she recognised as finality.'
  - '"My time is the sun''s time. When the light leaves the arena, I return to what
    I was. It is enough. I have said what I was placed here to say."'
  - 'He reached into his own breastplate and produced a coin. Old. Worn. The face
    on it had been rubbed smooth by centuries of touch, but the crest on the reverse
    was still sharp: the emblem of an empire, authoritative and permanent.'
  - "\"It's the Ancient Coin \u2014 minted by an empire that no longer exists. It
    opens one door only: the entrance to the final temple. It cannot be copied, forged,
    or stolen.\""
  - The final temple lies ahead. A maze. A last guardian unlike any you have faced.
    Insert this at the entrance. Trust what you know."
  - '"Remember: the pen only answers to someone who has never stopped believing that
    learning is worth everything."'
  - He finished the line as he walked back to his dais.
  textSpeed: 0.05
  playerTag: Player
  triggerOnce: 1
